RACE.RACE_TEXT: Amadevil S. COLUMBUS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 79. Stakes Purse 15800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD, BRED IN NEBRASKA. Purse $15,000-added. No nomination fee with $50 to pass the entry box and an additional $50 to start. With $15,000-added of which 60% of the total monies to the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 5% to f ourth and 3% to fifth. Weights: 3-year-olds 123 lbs., Older 125 lbs. Non-winners of $9,000 twice in 2022-23 allowed 3 lbs.; Of $9,000 in 2022-23, 5 lbs. Maiden, Claiming and Starter races not considered in allowances. High Weights Preferred, on the scale. Total earnings in 2022-23 will be used in determining the order of preference of horses assigned equal weights. Closed Tuesday, Sept. 26 with twelve nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAME THE PRICE moved to a clear early lead, was challenged into the far turn, dug in through the lane and kept PHLASH DRIVE safe to the wire. PHLASH DRIVE bid three wide outside the winner into the lane but could not get by. JUDGE'S BRIBE was in reach of the pace two or three wide, angled out into the lane to bid but could not get to the top pair. FOR REEL saved ground and made a mild late bid. KENHEDOIT was in reach three to four wide and lacked a final closing run. BARTENDERS MISTAKE failed to mount a rally three wide. no factor. L B GOLD dropped back three or four wide, angled in going to the far turn but was not a factor. J PS HARLEY GLIDER stumbled at the break, dropped back going to the first turn and pulled up on the backstretch then walked off under his own power.
